# Document boundaries

- One document — one responsibility.
- **spec** is not duplicated in status; status does not contain normative contract.
- **design** is not copied verbatim into spec.
- **ADR** is not edited as if it were the current specification; it records why.
- **Testing doc** does not copy system spec; it references spec and defines test model and run modes.
- **status** (project-status.md) only summarises current state: stages, in progress, planned, blockers. No long archives, no full test plan, no stage-by-stage implementation notes. Detailed content belongs in spec/, design/, testing/, adr/.
